  "texts": [
    "Multi-threshold metrics, such as area under the receiver operating characteristic curve (AUROC), are therefore based on varying the cutoff, which enables the explicit analysis of the trade-off between competing properties such as sensitivity and specificity.",
    "While most research in biomedical image analysis focuses on the discrimination capabilities of classifiers, a complementary important property is the calibration of a model.",
    "An uncertainty-aware model should yield predicted class scores that represent the true likelihood of events 28, as detailed in Supplementary Note 2.6.",
    "Overoptimistic or underoptimistic classifiers can be especially problematic in prediction tasks where a clinical decision may be made based on the risk of the patient developing a certain condition.",
    "Metrics Reloaded hence provides recommendations for validating the algorithm performance both in terms of discrimination and calibration."
  ],
